Introduction

Baby V.O.X is a five-member girl group under BABY VOX Co., Ltd. Formed by DR Music, they debuted on July 3, 1997 with their first studio album Equalizeher.

The original lineup consisted of Jeong Hyeonjeon, Jung Shiwoon, Cha Yumi, Kim EZ & Lee Heejin. Cha Yumi had to leave in the middle of the debut promotions and was then replaced by Kan Miyoun. After the groups debut promotions, the oldest members Jung Shiwoon and Jeong Hyeonjeon was replaced by Lee Gai and Shim Eunjin in 1998.

After DR MUSIC got exposed for lying about Lee Gai's age, she was replaced by Yoon Eunhye and the groups most famous lineup was created.

In 2004 Shim Eunjin left the agency and Baby V.O.X, followed by Yoon Eunhye and Kim EZ. The group officially disbanded in 2006.

On December 12, 2024, it was announced that Baby V.O.X will reunite on stage for the first time in 14 years on KBS’s End of the Year Broadcast for the special stage that highlights different generations of K-Pop.
